(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
(- SQL: The main topic being studied, understood here as sql is used to query and manage) Tj
T*
(data in relational databases.) Tj
T*
(- Core Focus: The main idea the learner must understand in this lesson: SELECT, INSERT,) Tj
T*
(UPDATE, DELETE, and filtering data.) Tj
T*
(- Application: The point where the explanation is used in practice, such as writing a) Tj
T*
(query to retrieve students with a certain score.) Tj
T*
(- Common Error: A repeated learner difficulty in this topic, for example forgetting) Tj
T*
(conditions or selecting the wrong field.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of SQL: SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, and filtering) Tj
T*
(data.) Tj
T*
(- Forgetting conditions or selecting the wrong field.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising SQL without checking whether the method matches the question being asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
