T*
(- In your own words, what does SQL mean in Computer Science?) Tj
T*
(- What part of this lesson explains SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, and filtering data) Tj
T*
(most clearly?) Tj
T*
(- Why is writing a query to retrieve students with a certain score a good example for) Tj
T*
(studying SQL?) Tj
T*
(- How would you avoid the mistake described as forgetting conditions or selecting the) Tj
T*
(wrong field?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips After Reading) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of SQL in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around basic query writing before trying harder tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as forgetting conditions or selecting the wrong field and) Tj
T*
(write the correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise SQL regularly so the method behind SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, and) Tj
T*
(filtering data becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Independent Practice) Tj
T*
(- Explain the overview of SQL and describe how it fits into Computer Science.) Tj
T*
(- Work through an example based on writing a query to retrieve students with a certain) Tj
T*
(score and explain each step.) Tj
T*
(- Describe why forgetting conditions or selecting the wrong field causes errors and how) Tj
T*
(to avoid it.) Tj
T*
(- Answer an exam-style question that focuses on basic query writing.) Tj
